2. Local modifications (`lean2.patch`)

---

`lean2.patch` is a Derivative Work of the upstream Lean 2 sources, authored
by IntGrah (2025-2026) and licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
It modifies the following files in `lean2/`:

    src/library/export.cpp
    src/util/lp/permutation_matrix.h
    src/util/lp/static_matrix.cpp
    src/util/lp/static_matrix.h

The modifications introduce a common-subexpression-elimination pass over
elaborated declaration bodies, extend the `#export` format with a `#EZ`
entry to serialise the kernel `let`-expressions the pass produces, and fix
unrelated C++ compatibility issues in the LP utilities that prevent the
upstream tree from building on modern compilers. Per Apache 2.0 section
4(b), this NOTICE constitutes the prominent notice that the files listed
above are modified relative to upstream; the upstream copyright headers in
those files are retained per section 4(c).

